    "shortDescription": "<p><i>Remove <i>curse</i></i> can remove all <i>curse</i>s on an object or a creature. If the target is a creature, you must make a caster level check (1d20 + caster level) against the DC of each <i>curse</i> affecting the target.</p><p>Success means that the <i>curse</i> is removed. <i>Remove <i>curse</i></i> does not remove the <i>curse</i> from a <i>curse</i>d shield, weapon, or suit of armor, although a successful caster level check enables the creature afflicted with any such <i>curse</i>d item to remove and get rid of it.</p><p><i>Remove <i>curse</i></i> counters and dispels bestow <i>curse</i>.</p>"
